    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but even if i rest, the reality is still there when i wake up. the debt, the shame, the feeling that i've wasted my entire life. it feels like a loop i can't escape. when i say i want to \"stop everything,\" i don't mean a vacation or a nap. i mean i want the noise to just end. forever. like, if i could just opt out of the whole struggle, wouldn't that be a more merciful way to handle all this pain?",
